text: *Horrible Bosses 2* I was in two minds about seeing this after reading some pretty lacklustre reviews, but I shouldn't have been worried. Just as enjoyable and laugh out loud funny as the first one, while gloriously lacking that "sequel for the sake of a sequel" feel (a bit like _22 Jump Street_ in that regard). The chemistry between the three leads has created a gold mine of comedic opportunities, and the tie ins to the first movie through joke call-backs and cameos was really well done. Should there be a third sequel, I earnestly hope they don't go all _Hangover 3_ with it.
